    <td width="400" bgcolor="#333333" height="84"> 
      <blockquote> 
        <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><b><br>
          <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3">DECCA and RCA</font></b></font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#CCCCCC">In 
          April 1976 Decca (London) presented this new recording which is a reference 
          in it own right - as the 1951 Lehman/Lieberson recording was in the 
          monaural years. But now with many cuts restored like the rap of Maria, 
          addressing Sportin' Life the morning after the death of Robbins. That 
          is prfobably the earliest rap performed on stage.</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
          </font></p>
      </blockquote>
